{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012RUnkCp2N7R6YFtKpnKq8F","type":"tool_result","content":"{\"body\":\"We would like users to be able to use metrics from other packages in `score()`. Sometimes, functions from those packages are different from our formats. \\n\\n- **0/1 input in binary scores**\\nOne example is functions to score binary forecasts that accept a numeric 0/1 vector for the observed value. Using those functions in `score()` would probably not work, as the input there is a factor. \\n\\n- **Functions that swap observed and predicted**\\nSome packages use `function(predicted, observed)` instead of our `function(observed, predicted)`. \\n\\nWe could think about providing a wrapper functions that would allow users to make use of these functions. \\n\\nWhat should those functions look like? What should they be called? \\n\\n```\\nwrap_binary_numeric <- function(observed, predicted, ..., fun) {\\n    observed <- as.numeric(observed) - 1\\n    do.call(fun, list(observed, predicted, ...))\\n}\\n```\\n\\n```\\nwrap_switch_order <- function(observed, predicted, ..., fun) {\\n    do.call(fun, list(predicted, observed, ...))\\n}\\n\\nSomething like this? \",\"comments\":[],\"title\":\"Discussion: design interface for external functions with different input/output formats\"}","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8e8f5457-0521-488c-ae9d-60ad5e963fe0","uuid":"9bda0eed-0868-44e3-9a6b-1c38fff86c70","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"{\"body\":\"We would like users to be able to use metrics from other packages in `score()`. Sometimes, functions from those packages are different from our formats. \\n\\n- **0/1 input in binary scores**\\nOne example is functions to score binary forecasts that accept a numeric 0/1 vector for the observed value. Using those functions in `score()` would probably not work, as the input there is a factor. \\n\\n- **Functions that swap observed and predicted**\\nSome packages use `function(predicted, observed)` instead of our `function(observed, predicted)`. \\n\\nWe could think about providing a wrapper functions that would allow users to make use of these functions. \\n\\nWhat should those functions look like? What should they be called? \\n\\n```\\nwrap_binary_numeric <- function(observed, predicted, ..., fun) {\\n    observed <- as.numeric(observed) - 1\\n    do.call(fun, list(observed, predicted, ...))\\n}\\n```\\n\\n```\\nwrap_switch_order <- function(observed, predicted, ..., fun) {\\n    do.call(fun, list(predicted, observed, ...))\\n}\\n\\nSomething like this? \",\"comments\":[],\"title\":\"Discussion: design interface for external functions with different input/output formats\"}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
