{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01D1wGdwGLx6yhEU82KitdQN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→#' @title Select metrics from a list of functions\n     2→#'\n     3→#' @description\n     4→#' Helper function to return only the scoring rules selected by\n     5→#' the user from a list of possible functions.\n     6→#'\n     7→#' @param metrics A list of scoring functions.\n     8→#' @param select A character vector of scoring rules to select from the list. If\n     9→#'   `select` is `NULL` (the default), all possible scoring rules are returned.\n    10→#' @param exclude A character vector of scoring rules to exclude from the list.\n    11→#'   If `select` is not `NULL`, this argument is ignored.\n    12→#' @returns A list of scoring functions.\n    13→#' @keywords handle-metrics\n    14→#' @importFrom checkmate assert_subset assert_list\n    15→#' @export\n    16→#' @examples\n    17→#' select_metrics(\n    18→#'   metrics = get_metrics(example_binary),\n    19→#'   select = \"brier_score\"\n    20→#' )\n    21→#' select_metrics(\n    22→#'   metrics = get_metrics(example_binary),\n    23→#'   exclude = \"log_score\"\n    24→#' )\n    25→select_metrics <- function(metrics, select = NULL, exclude = NULL) {\n    26→  assert_character(x = c(select, exclude), null.ok = TRUE)\n    27→  assert_list(metrics, names = \"named\")\n    28→  allowed <- names(metrics)\n    29→\n    30→  if (is.null(select) && is.null(exclude)) {\n    31→    return(metrics)\n    32→  }\n    33→  if (is.null(select)) {\n    34→    assert_subset(exclude, allowed)\n    35→    select <- allowed[!allowed %in% exclude]\n    36→    return(metrics[select])\n    37→  }\n    38→  assert_subset(select, allowed)\n    39→  return(metrics[select])\n    40→}\n    41→\n    42→#' Get metrics\n    43→#'\n    44→#' @description\n    45→#' Generic function to to obtain default metrics available for scoring or metrics\n    46→#' that were used for scoring.\n    47→#'\n    48→#' - If called on a `forecast` object it returns a list of functions that can be\n    49→#' used for scoring.\n    50→#' - If called on a `scores` object (see [score()]), it returns a character vector\n    51→#' with the names of the metrics that were used for scoring.\n    52→#'\n    53→#' See the documentation for the actual methods in the `See Also` section below\n    54→#' for more details. Alternatively call `?get_metrics.<forecast_type>` or\n    55→#' `?get_metrics.scores`.\n    56→#'\n    57→#' @param x A `forecast` or `scores` object.\n    58→#' @param ... Additional arguments passed to the method.\n    59→#'\n    60→#' @family get_metrics functions\n    61→#' @keywords handle-metrics\n    62→#' @export\n    63→get_metrics <- function(x, ...) {\n    64→  UseMethod(\"get_metrics\")\n    65→}\n    66→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01At9ss5uEU3jgBq14SwKQkw","session_id":"8e8f5457-0521-488c-ae9d-60ad5e963fe0","uuid":"c81c7c59-669d-4a9a-b866-e66705510c5b"}
